Sentencas: In this paper, a transient heat transfer model to simulate the heat-up and start-up periods of co- and counter-flow direct internal reforming solid oxide fuel cells is developed and presented.
Titulo: Heat-up and start-up modeling of direct internal reforming solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this comprehensive model, all the heat transfer mechanisms, i.e. conduction, convection, and radiation, and all the polarization nodes, i.e. ohmic, activation, and concentration, are considered.
Titulo: Heat-up and start-up modeling of direct internal reforming solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The heat transfer model is validated using the results of a benchmark test and two numerical studies obtained from the literature.
Titulo: Heat-up and start-up modeling of direct internal reforming solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: After validating the model, the heat-up, start-up, and steady-state behaviors of the cell are investigated.
Titulo: Heat-up and start-up modeling of direct internal reforming solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In addition, the first principal thermal stresses are calculated to find the probability of failure of the cell during its operation.
Titulo: Heat-up and start-up modeling of direct internal reforming solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results of the present model are in good agreement with the literature data.
Titulo: Heat-up and start-up modeling of direct internal reforming solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It is also shown for the given input data that counter-flow case yields a higher average current density and power density, but a lower electrical efficiency of the cell.
Titulo: Heat-up and start-up modeling of direct internal reforming solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: For the temperature controlled heat-up and start-up strategy, the maximum probability of failure during the operation of the cell is found to be 0.068% and 0.078% for co- and counter-flow configurations, respectively.
Titulo: Heat-up and start-up modeling of direct internal reforming solid oxide fuel cells
